# AE Ladder Results Dashboard — Wiring Spec & Build Guide

**Version:** 1.0  
**Status:** Ready for Antigravity build  
**Supabase View:** `vw_ae_dashboard_results`  
**Primary Table:** `ae_assessment_insights`  
**Supporting Tables:** `ae_assessments`, `ae_dimension_scores`, `ae_dimension_band_stage_meanings`

---

## Overview

This document defines the complete field mapping, component structure, and incremental build sequence for the AE Ladder Results Dashboard. It serves as the permanent technical reference for how the dashboard is wired and as the step-by-step Antigravity build instruction.

The dashboard renders results from a single Supabase view query:

```sql
SELECT * FROM vw_ae_dashboard_results
WHERE ae_assessment_id = '<current_user_assessment_id>'
```

All dashboard sections bind their content directly to named fields from this view. No additional transformation or secondary queries are needed for dashboard rendering.

---

## Part 1 — Technical Spec

### 1.1 Data Source

**View:** `vw_ae_dashboard_results`

This view joins the following tables into a single flat result:

| Source Table | What It Contributes |
|---|---|
| `ae_assessments` | Assessment identity, overall score, submitted_at |
| `ae_frontend_stages` | Stage label, tagline, description |
| `ae_assessment_insights` | All GPT-generated narrative content + signal headlines |
| `ae_dimension_scores` | Per-dimension avg scores and band IDs |
| `ae_dimension_band_stage_meanings` | Deterministic meaning text, signal tags, focus areas |

Query pattern for the dashboard component:

```typescript
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('vw_ae_dashboard_results')
  .select('*')
  .eq('ae_assessment_id', assessmentId)
  .single()
```

---

### 1.2 Dashboard Section Map

The dashboard is structured into six sections. Each section lists its fields, their source in the view, the collapsed default state, and the expanded state where applicable.

---

#### SECTION 1 — Hero

**Purpose:** Stage identity, overall score, and strategic orientation

**Collapsed state — always visible:**

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Stage tagline | `ae_stage_tagline` | Bold headline |
| Stage interpretation | `stage_brief_interpretation` | 1–2 sentence subheading |
| Overall score | `overall_score` | Numeric display |
| Stage label | `ae_frontend_stage` | Badge or label |

**Expanded state — revealed on user interaction:**

| UI Element | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Strategic overview paragraph | `strategic_insights_overall` | 2–4 sentence GPT synthesis |

---

#### SECTION 2 — Dimension Snapshot

**Purpose:** Per-dimension score and band, with expandable meaning context

Five cards, one per dimension. All five follow the same pattern.

**Dimension to view field mapping:**

| Dimension | avg field | band_label field | band_stage_meaning field | signal_tag field | primary_focus field | secondary_focus field |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Financial & Business Health | `financial_avg` | `financial_band_label` | `financial_band_stage_meaning` | `financial_signal_tag` | `financial_primary_focus` | `financial_secondary_focus` |
| Client Base & Positioning | `client_avg` | `client_band_label` | `client_band_stage_meaning` | `client_signal_tag` | `client_primary_focus` | `client_secondary_focus` |
| Operational Systems | `ops_avg` | `ops_band_label` | `ops_band_stage_meaning` | `ops_signal_tag` | `ops_primary_focus` | `ops_secondary_focus` |
| Team & Leadership | `team_avg` | `team_band_label` | `team_band_stage_meaning` | `team_signal_tag` | `team_primary_focus` | `team_secondary_focus` |
| Strategic Stewardship | `stewardship_avg` | `stewardship_band_label` | `stewardship_band_stage_meaning` | `stewardship_signal_tag` | `stewardship_primary_focus` | `stewardship_secondary_focus` |

**Collapsed state — always visible per card:**

- Dimension name (static label)
- `{dimension}_avg` — numeric score
- `{dimension}_band_label` — band name

**Expanded state — revealed on card interaction:**

- `{dimension}_band_stage_meaning` — paragraph text block
- `{dimension}_signal_tag` — rendered as a small chip or tag
- `{dimension}_primary_focus` — rendered as a chip
- `{dimension}_secondary_focus` — rendered as a chip

Chips are display-only. No interaction required on chips.

---

#### SECTION 3 — Agency Signal Identity

**Purpose:** Compressed, scannable read of the agency's current momentum posture

This section **replaces** the previous card grid. It renders as a content block: one short paragraph followed by three declarative headline bullets.

**Field mapping:**

| UI Element | View Field | Format |
|---|---|---|
| Stage description paragraph | `ae_stage_description` | Static paragraph, pulled from stage reference |
| Strength headline | `signal_headline_strength` | Single declarative bullet |
| Friction headline | `signal_headline_friction` | Single declarative bullet |
| Synthesis headline | `signal_headline_synthesis` | Single declarative bullet |

**Rendering notes:**
- The three headlines render as styled list items, not as prose
- Each headline is one sentence, 10–18 words
- No expand/collapse needed on this section — it is always fully visible
- If any of the three headline fields are null (GPT not yet fired), render a neutral placeholder: `—` or leave the bullet row empty rather than showing a broken state

---

#### SECTION 4 — Core Strengths & Primary Gaps

**Purpose:** GPT-generated narrative interpretation of each dimension's current operating state

One paragraph per dimension, rendered in a list or stacked card layout.

**Field mapping:**

| Dimension | View Field |
|---|---|
| Financial & Business Health | `dimension_insight_financials` |
| Client Base & Positioning | `dimension_insight_client_base` |
| Operational Systems | `dimension_insight_ops` |
| Team & Leadership | `dimension_insight_team` |
| Strategic Stewardship | `dimension_insight_founder_role` |

**Rendering notes:**
- Each paragraph is 2–3 sentences of GPT-generated text
- Render in the same visual order as the Dimension Snapshot cards above
- If a field is null, render an empty state: `"Insights generating..."` or similar

---

#### SECTION 5 — Strategic Focus Priorities

**Purpose:** Four engine-selected strategic callouts directing the founder's attention

Renders as four distinct cards or blocks, each with a bold headline and body text.

**Field mapping:**

| Priority | View Field | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Focus Priority 1 | `focus_point_1` | Primary leverage dimension |
| Focus Priority 2 | `focus_point_2` | Primary friction dimension |
| Focus Priority 3 | `focus_point_3` | Stage posture / evolution cue |
| Focus Priority 4 | `focus_point_4` | Pattern-level synthesis |

**Rendering notes:**
- Each focus point field contains a full string with bold headline and body text as returned by GPT
- If the field contains a structured headline + body pattern, parse and render the headline in bold and the body below it
- If fields are null, render empty state cards rather than hiding the section

---

#### SECTION 6 — Report Download CTA

**Purpose:** Link to the generated PDF report

**Field mapping:**

| UI Element | Source | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Download button | Signed URL from `ae_assessments.report_pdf_url` or equivalent | Existing logic — no change needed |

This section requires no changes as part of this build.

