## Part 3 — n8n Workflow Connection Notes

Once the dashboard build is complete, the n8n workflow must be updated to write the three new signal headline fields to `ae_assessment_insights`. The Supabase insert node in n8n should map:

| GPT Response Path | Supabase Column |
|---|---|
| `outputs.signal_headlines.signal_headline_strength` | `signal_headline_strength` |
| `outputs.signal_headlines.signal_headline_friction` | `signal_headline_friction` |
| `outputs.signal_headlines.signal_headline_synthesis` | `signal_headline_synthesis` |

No other changes to the n8n workflow are required. All other insight fields are already mapped. Once n8n fires for a completed assessment, the view will automatically return the populated fields and the dashboard will render live content without any additional dashboard changes.

